job-step.description: Topic Inbound consumes tuples from a specified topic in the DPC and emits them to be processed by downstream job steps.
Formatter uses a FreeMarker template to build a single string from the input tuple values, and sends the converted string to a downstream job step.

JSON Normalization takes a single JSON object that was received as a string value and extracts various values. For each extracted value, it then adds a field to the tuple emitted to the output stream.
Read-only Contextual Profile reads an existing profile, calls a script to glean insights from the profile, and generates fields with the results of the profile analysis.

parameter.name: generator-function-FIELD

job-step.description: Python Model allows you to use serialized, trained Python models to perform simple to complex analytics against data in the input stream.

Contextual Profile can use raw and derived attributes as real-time context attributes, capture this context in a profile, and use the profile dynamically to continuously detect and act on patterns in the stream. To use this job step, you must also configure Job-Level Parameters to specify the Profile Store Group Name.

Script executes a supported native language script and passes the results to the next job step. You can use this job step to, for example, perform currency conversions, normalize data, or perform calculations and limit checking.
Topic Outbound receives input fields from the previous job step, and then generates tuples and sends them to the topic associated with the job step.
Visualization Store collects batches of incoming tuples and writes them to a visualization store where the information they contain can be viewed through the Visualization dashboard.
